\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 (18:2) }{\f0\fs24\b1\cb5\highlight5 Theophany}{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 : before Christ came, God spoke to men \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93in many ways\u8221\'94 (He. 1:1). As an example, He sometimes appeared:}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx720\li720\fi-360\sb180\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab in human form (Ge. 3:8; 5:24; 6:9; 18:1\endash 33).}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx720\li720\fi-360\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab in some form of majestic glory (Ezk 1:1\endash 28, esp. 26\endash 28; Is. 6:1\endash 13; see note\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Ge. 16:7; see Ex. 3:2; Jos. 5:13\endash 15; Jud. 2:1\endash 5).}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\fi360\sb180\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 Such appearances are called theophanies. In simple terms, a theophany is a visible appearance of God to man, usually in a human form.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge18.2-8&off=5986&ctx=e%E2%80%9D+(1+Ti.+6:17%E2%80%9318).%0a~Deeper+Study+%23+1%0a(18"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 91). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
