\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs32\b1 5}{\f0\fs24  (18:11\endash 15) }{\f0\fs24\b1 Unbelief\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Lying\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 God, Power; Knowledge of}{\f0\fs24 : How can we become a friend of God? Conquer unbelief. Note three significant things.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 a. The causes of unbelief are clearly seen in this experience of Sarah.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 1)\tab Sarah and Abraham were looking at an impossible situation, humanly speaking. They were both beyond childbearing years. Abraham was one hundred years old and Sarah was ninety years old.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 2)\tab Sarah allowed negative thoughts to enter her mind. As stated above, she had heard the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promise to Abraham, but she knew the impossible circumstances. The whole situation just seemed laughable to Sarah, and she actually laughed to herself, somewhat mockingly and skeptically. She murmured silently to herself, \u8220\'93How can I who am so old have the pleasure of sex and bear a child, and Abraham also being so old\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 impossible! A laugh!\u8221\'94 Sarah was responding to God\u8217\'92s promise in unbelief: she just did not believe God\u8217\'92s promise, did not believe it was possible. It was physically impossible to her. Note that she was thinking of the circumstances, not thinking of God and His promise and power.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 b. The answer to unbelief is twofold (vv. 13\endash 14).}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 1)\tab }{\f0\fs24\i1 God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s omniscience}{\f0\fs24 , His knowing all things. God asked Abraham why Sarah had laughed, revealing that He knew all about Sarah\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s unbelief.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 2)\tab }{\f0\fs24\i1 God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s omnipotence}{\f0\fs24 , His power to do all things (v. 14). \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Is anything too hard for the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 (v. 14). God can do anything, no matter how impossible it seems. He clearly said that He would give Sarah a child despite her dead womb (see Ro. 4:19).}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I know that thou canst do every thing, and that no thought can be withholden from thee\u8221\'94 (Jb. 42:2)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But Jesus beheld [them], and said unto them, With men this is impossible; but with God all things are possible\u8221\'94 (Mt. 19:26)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93For with God nothing shall be impossible\u8221\'94 (Lu. 1:37)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 c. The conquest of unbelief (v. 15). Sarah lied: she denied that she had laughed, for she feared a severe rebuke from the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  and perhaps from Abraham. But the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  made it clear: she did laugh\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 laughed in unbelief\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 and He knew all about her failure to believe the promise of the promised seed. Moreover, she was now lying about the matter.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 What the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  was doing was telling Sarah that she needed to confess, repent, stop the deceit and lying, and believe the promise. God could perform the miracle, overcome the circumstances of life, no matter how impossible they might appear. God could fulfill His promise. Sarah could conquer unbelief only if she confessed, repented, and believed the promise of the promised seed.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24 . Unbelief will always keep us from being a friend of God. The friend of God believes God; he never disbelieves. We must, therefore, conquer unbelief:}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab We must not look at circumstances as though they are impossible for God.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab We must not allow negative thoughts to surround the promises of God, questioning His promises.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab We must believe that God knows all and can do all.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab We must confess and repent of our sin of unbelief, of distrusting the promises of God.}
