\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (18:16\endash 33) }{\f0\fs24\b1 Introduction\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Prayer\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Intercession}{\f0\fs24 : God wanted Abraham to do something special, very special. God wanted Abraham to become an }{\f0\fs24\i1 intercessor}{\f0\fs24 , that is, a believer who struggles and wrestles in prayer for others, and who does it often. The words }{\f0\fs24\i1 struggle, wrestle}{\f0\fs24 , and }{\f0\fs24\i1 often}{\f0\fs24  are the key words. God wants believers who will pray often\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 constantly-believers who will struggle and wrestle in prayer for people and for the needs of the world.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The Lord is not slack concerning his promise, as some men count slackness; but is longsuffering to us-ward, not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to repentance\u8221\'94 (2 Pe. 3:9)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 How do we become }{\f0\fs24\i1 intercessors}{\f0\fs24 ? Get alone and focus our thoughts and prayers upon people in need, upon both the unbelievers and believers of the world. When prayer is approached with strong concentration of thought, when the world is completely shut out, prayer often becomes intense. One just becomes deeply conscious of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s presence and deeply conscious of the needs of others and of the world. The believer begins to struggle for others, for the needs of the world. He draws near God and near those for whom he is praying. He senses that both God and others are ever so near. He loves God and loves those for whom he is praying\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 loves them ever so intensely. He wrestles with God for them, not because God is hard to reach and unconcerned and must be struggled against, but because he feels so much concern and so much love that he just pours out his heart to God. In the process, the prayer warrior is drawing much closer to God and gaining a much deeper concern for man! He is learning to love God more and to love man more, and this is exactly what God wants. God wants believers to be near Him and near others; to love God and others\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to live both for God and for others; to be both God-centered and man-centered.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Just think of the impact upon this world\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the enormous impact for good\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 if enough believers would become intercessors!}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Note one other fact as well. God knew exactly what was going to happen to Sodom before this event with Abraham took place. He knew that Lot was the only righteous person in the city. What then was God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s purpose in leading Abraham to intercede in prayer time and time again? God\u8217\'92s purpose was at least threefold:}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 First, to teach Abraham\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 and all others who followed him\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to become intercessors, prayer warriors, for both the righteous and wicked of the earth.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 Second, to teach Abraham\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 and all others who followed him\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 that God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s justice must be executed. Every human being will face the judgment of God.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 Third, to teach Abraham\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 and all others who followed him\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to become stronger witnesses for Him. Abraham had been a strong witness to Lot and, no doubt, to his family. Abraham had taken Lot in as a child when Lot\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s father had died, treated him as a son, given him first choice of the land, and saved him from an invading army, risking his own life. But, Abraham was bound to think, after this experience of judgment upon Sodom, if he had been a stronger witness to Lot\u8217\'92s family, perhaps some would have been saved.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 Now, the subject of this great passage is: }{\f0\fs24\i1 Abraham Was Visited by God Himself (Part 2): Intercessory Faith\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the Steps to Becoming an Intercessor, a Prayer Warrior}{\f0\fs24 , 18:16\endash 33.}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 1.\tab Step 1: yearning to walk with God step by step, longing for His presence (v. 16).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 2.\tab Step 2: thinking of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s great call and purpose for one\u8217\'92s life (vv. 17\endash 19).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 3.\tab Step 3: sensing the pain of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s heart over wickedness (vv. 20\endash 21).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 4.\tab Step 4: standing boldly before the Lord in prayer\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 refusing to leave the Lord\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s presence (vv. 22\endash 26).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 5.\tab Step 5: laying hold of the open access (door) into God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s presence (vv. 27\endash 28).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 6.\tab Step 6: continuing to pray and beseech God, praying on and on and never giving up (v. 29).}
\par\pard\plain \tx720\li720\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 7.\tab Step 7: persevering in concern and prayer (vv. 30\endash 33).\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge18.16-33&off=4621&ctx=r+Warrior%2c+18:16%E2%80%9333%0a~(18:16%E2%80%9333)+Introduct"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, pp. 93\endash 94). Chattanooga, T\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
