\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Intercession}{\f0\fs24 : How does a person become an intercessor, a prayer warrior? By yearning to walk with God step by step, longing for His presence. Remember, the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  and two angels had appeared to Abraham at the door of his tent, and they had spent a good deal of time with him. Now the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  and the two angels arose, looked down toward Sodom, and began to walk toward the city. Note, Abraham joined them. He did not have to follow them; he could have stayed behind at his tent. But this he did not do. Abraham joined the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  as He walked away to begin the journey toward Sodom. Why? Because Abraham just did not want to leave the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s presence. He had tasted (experienced) the closest bond of friendship imaginable with the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab a strong sense of friendship and fellowship with God (Ge. 18:1\endash 8)}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab a strong assurance of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promises (Ge. 18:10\endash 14)}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab a deep awareness of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s unlimited power (Ge. 18:10)}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 The deep sense of friendship, fellowship, and assurance of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s power all swelled up within Abraham\u8217\'92s heart, and he just did not want the experience to end. He wanted to spend as much time as he could in God\u8217\'92s presence so he walked along with the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  step by step.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24 . A true intercessor wants to walk along with the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  step by step and longs for God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s presence. He yearns to develop the closest, most intimate friendship possible with the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24 . Therefore, he seeks and makes opportunity \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab to turn his thoughts to the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  throughout the day.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab to captivate every thought, focusing upon things that are true, honest, just, pure, lovely, and of a good report (Ph. 4:8).}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab to set aside blocks of time for concentrated, uninterrupted prayer\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 every day.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Simply stated, the intercessor wants and longs for God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s presence, to walk along with God step by step, all day and all night long.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge18.16&off=10&ctx=.+30%E2%80%9333).%0a1+(18:16)+~Intercession:+How+do"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 94). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Believer, Duty}{\f0\fs24 : How does a person become an intercessor, a prayer warrior? By thinking of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s great call and purpose for one\u8217\'92s life. Note what the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  did: He spoke softly to Himself, yet loud enough so that Abraham could hear (see v. 23). Why? There are three reasons.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 a. Abraham needed to think of his God-given call and purpose (v. 18). He was to father a great and powerful nation; moreover, all the nations of the earth were to be blessed through him, through the promised seed, the Savior of the world, who was to be a descendant of his. Note what God was arousing within Abraham: a sense of responsibility for the world. God was about to execute His justice upon Sodom and Gomorrah\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 destroy it\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 because of their terrible wickedness. God wanted Abraham to sense a responsibility for both the righteous and the wicked; God wanted Abraham stirred to intercede\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to struggle and wrestle in prayer\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 for the cities of the earth. Abraham had a }{\f0\fs24\i1 responsibility}{\f0\fs24 \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a part\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 in the lives of his fellow men, both the righteous and the wicked. He must, therefore, be aroused to pray for them, even to the point of struggling in prayer.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 b. Abraham needed to think of his duty to teach the ways of the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24 , to teach what is right and just (v. 19). Abraham was soon to witness the justice of God falling upon Sodom and Gomorrah. God wanted Abraham to understand God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s ways, that He always does what is right and just, and God wanted Abraham to teach the ways of God. Thus God reminded Abraham of his teaching duties, reminded him right before the destruction of Sodom and Gomorrah.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24 c. Abraham needed to think of faithfulness and of the reward for being faithful. God made great promises to Abraham, and He was going to bring about these promises. But Abraham needed to remember: he was to be faithful; he was to teach the ways of the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24 . Then and only then would the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  reward him; then and only then would Abraham receive the promises.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24 . Focusing upon the same three subjects will stir us to become intercessors for God:}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (1)\tab Thinking about God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s great call and purpose. God has called us to know the promised seed, the Savior, and to make Him known. We have a }{\f0\fs24\i1 responsibility}{\f0\fs24 , a part, in the lives of our fellow men, both the righteous and the wicked. We must, therefore, be aroused to pray for them, even to the point of struggling in prayer.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (2)\tab Thinking about our duty to teach the ways of the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24 . We need to pray and pray much\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 intercede for ourselves and for others\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 if we are going to teach the ways of God.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 (3)\tab Thinking about our great need to be faithful and the great reward promised us if we are faithful. We can never walk faithfully without God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s help; thus we need to be constantly praying, even interceding, for God\u8217\'92s help.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge18.17-19&off=13&ctx=10:5).%0a2+(18:17%E2%80%9319)+~Believer%2c+Duty:+How+"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 95). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab God wanted to teach all believers of succeeding generations to follow Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s example in crying out\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 in becoming intercessors\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 for the souls of people.}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab God wanted to teach all people that God is longsuffering and full of mercy, not willing that any person perish, but His mercy is open only to those who believe in Him and receive His mercy. Remember that God had given Sodom and Gomorrah every chance in the world to repent and turn to Him. They had a chance to repent when Abraham freed them from captivity to the invading army from the east (Ge. 14:1\endash 16; 14:17\endash 24); when Melchizedek, the priest of God, bore testimony to them (Ge. 14:18\endash 20); and through the testimony of Lot, weak as his witness was (2 Pe. 2:6\endash 9).}
\par\pard\plain \tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 \bullet \tab God wanted to teach all people that sin leads to judgment, and judgment will be executed. God is going to judge the world.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge18.20-21&off=1173&ctx=+cities.+Moreover+%E2%80%A6%0a~%E2%80%A2+God+wanted+to+teac"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, pp. 95\endash 96). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24 . How can we become an intercessor, a prayer warrior? By standing boldly before the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  in prayer and by appealing to His justice. God will always do what is right and just. God will never judge a person beyond that which he deserves. Every person will receive exactly what he deserves, nothing more and nothing less. God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s justice will be executed upon every person, but it will be perfect justice. God will do what is right and just, perfectly so.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Let us therefore come boldly unto the throne of grace, that we may obtain mercy, and find grace to help in time of need\u8221\'94 (He. 4:16)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93In whom we have boldness and access with confidence by the faith of him [Christ]\u8221\'94 (Ep. 3:12)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Having therefore, brethren, boldness to enter into the holiest by the blood of Jesus\u8221\'94 (He. 10:19)}{\f0\fs24 .\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge18.22-26&off=2196&ctx=ght+appeal+to+make.%0a~Thought+1.+How+can+w"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 96). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs32\b1 5}{\f0\fs24  (18:27\endash 28) }{\f0\fs24\b1 Access\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Prayer\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Intercession}{\f0\fs24 : How does a person become an intercessor, a prayer warrior? By laying hold of the open access\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the open door\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 into God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s presence. No doubt, all the wickedness within the cities began to engross Abraham\u8217\'92s mind, and he began to wonder if there were anywhere close to fifty righteous people within the city. Apparently, he felt that if he asked only for Lot and his dear family, he would be acting selfishly. And Abraham was not selfish, nor was he concerned only for Lot and his family. What could he do? How could he pray so that God would both save the city and understand that he was not selfish? There was only one way: keep praying and asking God for more and more until He said \u8220\'93No.\u8221\'94 But ask God in all humility. Note how Abraham approached the }{\f0\fs24\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24  this second time: confessing that he was but dust and ashes. And note the word }{\f0\fs24\i1 Lord}{\f0\fs24  (Adonai). This is not the personal name for }{\f0\fs24\i1 Lord}{\f0\fs24 , but rather the more formal title for God. Abraham was appealing to the }{\f0\fs24\i1 Lord}{\f0\fs24  who is the Sovereign Ruler and Judge of all the earth.}
\par\pard\plain \fi360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Abraham asked God to spare the city if forty-five righteous were found, and God answered his prayer.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24 . How can we become intercessors, prayer warriors? By approaching God in humility, as dust and ashes, and laying hold of God, laying hold of the open access and door into His presence.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge18.27-28&off=0&ctx=Jesus%E2%80%9D+(He.+10:19).%0a~5+(18:27%E2%80%9328)+Access%E2%80%94"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, pp. 96\endash 97). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\pard\plain \sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs32\b1 6}{\f0\fs24  (18:29) }{\f0\fs24\b1 Prayer\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Intercession}{\f0\fs24 : How does a person become an intercessor, a prayer warrior? By continuing in prayer, praying on and on and not giving up, but beseeching God. The verse and point is self-explanatory: Abraham asked God to spare the city if forty righteous people were found, and God answered his prayer.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24 . The true intercessor refuses to give up. He continues to pray on and on. This is exactly what Scripture tells us to do.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Seek the }{\f0\fs24\b1\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24\b1  and his strength, seek his face continually\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 (1 Chr. 16:11)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Ask, and it shall be given you; seek, and ye shall find; knock, and it shall be opened unto you\u8221\'94 (Mt. 7:7)}{\f0\fs24 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Watch [be sleepless] and pray, that ye enter not into temptation: the spirit indeed [is] willing, but the flesh [is] weak\u8221\'94 (Mt. 26:41)}{\f0\fs24 .\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge18.29&off=0&ctx=+hear%E2%80%9D+(Is.+65:24).%0a~6+(18:29)+Prayer%E2%80%94Int"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 97). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \li720\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Thought 1}{\f0\fs24 . Scripture assures us: if we persevere in prayer, God will hear and answer.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi360\ri360\sb180\qj\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And he spake a parable unto them to this end, that men ought always to pray, and not to faint\u8221\'94 (Lu. 18:1)}{\f0\fs24 .}
